@startuml

title Super Admin User Search and Filtering Sequence Diagram

actor "Super Admin" as Admin

participant "Frontend (Website)" as FE
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "UserController" as UC
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
end box

database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of Admin
Super Admin is the only role with access
to the Search Users page. From this page,
they can search users, filter by role,
and manage user accounts. They also have 
access to the entire website.
end note

note left of DB
It is assumed the Super Admin is
authenticated/authorized unless an exception occurs.
end note


== Open Search Users Page ==

Admin -> FE: Open "Buscar Usuarios" page
activate Admin
activate FE
activate Apache
activate MW
activate UC
activate ORM
activate DB

FE -> Apache: GET /search_user

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP search users request
else Route not found
    Apache --> FE: 404 Not Found
    FE --> Admin: Display "Search users route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> UC: Pass authenticated and authorized search users request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> FE: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden
    FE --> Admin: Display validation or authorization error
end

UC -> ORM: User::all()
ORM -> DB: SELECT * FROM users

alt User query success
    DB --> ORM: User result set
    ORM --> UC: users collection
    UC --> FE: Return search_user view
    FE --> Admin: Display user cards with role and status information
else User query failure
    DB --> ORM: Query failed / SQL exception
    ORM --> UC: User retrieval failed
    UC --> FE: 500 Internal Server Error
    FE --> Admin: Display system error while loading users
end


== Search and Filter Users ==

Admin -> FE: Search by name/email or filter by role

alt Matching users found
    FE --> Admin: Display filtered user cards and pagination
else No matching users found
    FE --> Admin: Display "No se encontraron usuarios"
end

@enduml